    {
      "name": "Dawg",
      "media_title": "Lobo",
      "tropes": [
        "AllLoveIsUnrequited",
        "ActionPet",
        "ADogNamedDog",
        "SubvertedTrope",
        "BullyBulldog",
        "AlienAnimals",
        "AllAnimalsAreDogs",
        "EvilDetectingDog",
        "Tanuki",
        "CanineCompanion",
        "LoyalAnimalCompanion",
        "CrapsackWorld"
      ],
      "description": "Action Pet: Not very often but Dawg has had its piece of the action here and there. Alien Animals: The pooch looks like an Earth's bulldog but is an alien. All Animals Are Dogs: And in its case, even looks like one. All Love Is Unrequited: Dawg's care for Lobo is not very often well reciprocated. Bully Bulldog:Subverted. For Dawg is, despite of its gruff appearance,waaaymore social and friendly than his master.",
      "source": "tvtropes"
    },
    {
      "name": "Darlene Spritzer",
      "media_title": "Lobo",
      "tropes": [
        "AllGirlsWantBadBoys",
        "AllLoveIsUnrequited",
        "ShoutOut",
        "MsFanservice",
        "BerserkButton",
        "HumanAliens",
        "JustFriends",
        "The90s"
      ],
      "description": "Darlene was a waitress at Al's. She is the main love interest of Lobo. All Girls Want Bad Boys: Although in her case it is only one-sided. Lobo likes her...very much, but he has never been willing to form a significative bond. All Love Is Unrequited: Lobo's exploits often leave her behind and down, nevertheless, she's always front and center for him. Berserk Button. Never,EVERdare to say Lobo and her areJust Friends... even if it is Lobo who says it over and over again. Human Aliens: She and Al may be human after all, but they always hang around in orbit.",
      "source": "tvtropes"
    },
    {
      "name": "Jonas Glim",
      "media_title": "Lobo",
      "tropes": [
        "HumanoidAliens",
        "HeterosexualLifePartners"
      ],
      "description": "A fellow bounty hunter and friend/rival of Lobo. Heterosexual Life-Partners: He is close friends with Lobo. Humanoid Aliens: He looks similar to a human with the exception of the huge tusks on his face.",
      "source": "tvtropes"
    },
