      "description": "Human Aliens: Like Darlene, he looks like a human but lives in space. Only Known by Their Nickname: Al is just a nickname and his full name is never revealed.",
      "source": "tvtropes"
    },
    {
      "name": "Billy the Girl",
      "media_title": "Lobo",
      "tropes": [
        "VaporWear",
        "BountyHunter",
        "NavelWindow",
        "HumanAliens"
      ],
      "description": "Bounty Hunter: Like Lobo she makes a living as a bounty hunter. Human Aliens: She looks just like a human, but like Lobo can breathe in space. Navel Window: Her outfit comes with an opening for her navel. Vapor Wear: Her outfit shows her hips and waist, indicating she's not wearing any underwear.",
      "source": "tvtropes"
    },
    {
      "name": "Goldstar",
      "media_title": "Lobo",
      "tropes": [
        "ExpyCoexistence",
        "ChestInsignia",
        "HumanAliens",
        "DominoMask",
        "OneSteveLimit",
        "SupermanSubstitute"
      ],
      "description": "Chest Insignia: A golden star. Domino Mask: Unlike Superman he wears a golden domino mask. Expy Coexistence: He's aSuperman Substitutewho exists on the same universe as the Man of Steel, although they never crossed paths. Human Aliens: Just like a Kryptonian, he's indistinguishable from a blonde-haired human. One-Steve Limit: Has nothing to do with Booster Gold's partner Gold Star.",
      "source": "tvtropes"
    },
